channel.title: Login to windows withouth prompt
channel.description:
I'm having a problem with this PC I got.
The PC is secured limited wise, I can't access C:\ or any other drive then the network drive. Nor can I change any thing system wise or program wise (the account is very limited). It's running Windows XP.
The problem is. Via dos I created a local admin account, which I want to use. However if you start the PC up XP gives you only three possibilities of accounts. 1: The limited account 2: Another limtied account 3: Admin account
Now I don't know the password of the Admin account, so I want to use the self created account. How do I manage to do that?
I got access to DOS, I can't use a USB or any other portable device.
Cleaning the whole PC isn't an option, I need the files.

item.title: Login to windows withouth prompt
item.dc:creator: @Waffendennis Waffendennis
item.description:
@Waffendennis wrote:

Fixed it with a different approach!

Somehow the old system admins ‘forgot’ to disable the MMC.
So I just changed the group policies and made sure the normal account which I had access too is changed to an Admin.

Thanks everyone.

item.title: Login to windows withouth prompt
item.dc:creator: @sppt sppt
item.description:
@sppt wrote:

If with DOS access you mean access to the command prompt, you could try doing this:

1. Open the Command Prompt (cmd.exe or command.com) 2.type "at hh:mm /interactive start explorer.exe" with hh:mm being a time in the future 3. type "tskill explorer" and hit enter. now wait until the clock reaches the specified time. You should now have access to the system account.
